examples.en: We carved an ice sculpture.
The jewel box had a carved wooden cover.
Father carved the ham.
The thieves carved up the profit from the robbery.
The chairs are carved in a rococo style.
His birthdate and date of death were carved on the stone.
She carved out her own niche in the industry.
The company carved $1 million from its budget.
The river had carved channels in the limestone rock.
She carved out a successful career in the film industry.
He carved out a name for himself in the engineering business.
A few strange words carved on a tree were the only vestige of the lost colony of Roanoke.
He carved while I made the gravy.
Europe was carved up after World War I.
He carved a niche for himself as a writer.
Skilled craftsmen carved the enormous mantel.
Someone had carved their initials on the tree.
Rosettes are carved in the base of the statue.
The emperor's tomb had his image carved in stone.
A carved cornice runs around the high-ceilinged room.
An angel watching an urn wept over her, carved in stone.
A stanza has a lapidary dignity, as of something carved in stone.
He had carved out a career as a procurer of high-priced call girls for wealthy, powerful men.
